inear regime is favored by observations and closer to the\nconcordance model due to the non-zero value of the parameter $j$, which\ncontrols the non linear effects. In fact, at low redshift values, the expansion\nrate associated to the full non linear regime is practically indistinguishable\nfrom $\\Lambda$CDM. The deceleration parameter obtained in this regime exhibits\na transition from decelerated to accelerated cosmic expansion.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 6 May 2022 04:08:16 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 1 Oct 2022 07:20:57 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-11-14"}
